narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: I learned to critically read and analyze theoretical texts an apply the concepts learned to current and future issues arising in the world.
The application of theory that might be up to hundred years old to present day. I found myself thinking about the topics of this course even outside the classroom- this is how interesting it all was!
I learned a lot about the world as a greater whole along with obtaining thought provoking knowledge.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: Strengths of this course include great class discussion and interesting/engaging course material. It could be improved by adding my variety in assignment selections.
The professor did a tremendous job keeping the class engaged and leading discussions. She brought forward very interesting topics and an inviting environment.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes, I would. This was my favorite class I've taken at Yale and was very interested and engaged all semester long.
Yes. Very insightful readings and paper topics that provoke thought.
